::GoldenEye::

She looked down and helped him walk.  She felt down.  She could sence 
his disapproval in her manner of helpfullness.  She just wasn't sure 
what to do.  folow the Predacon sode and let him die out here alone 
and all.  Or pass up the opertunity for some companionship and 
conversation,even for a little while.  She jsut didn't know what 
would be better.  She helped him hobble along seeing him get weaker 
as they went.

She sighed and looked at him. "If you need some energy,I can give you 
some of mine. We have a long way to go." she said in a soft and flat 
voice.  She didn't know why she even offered. Hadn't she helped this 
stranger enough?  Appearently not, she thought.
